    28Ôćĺ  This makes the orElse types match the implementation.
    29Ôćĺ
    30Ôćĺ  This is a breaking change for the orElse type argument list,
    31Ôćĺ  as the ok type must now be provided before the err type.
    32Ôćĺ
    33Ôćĺ  ```diff
    34Ôćĺ  - result.orElse<ErrType>(foo)
    35Ôćĺ  + result.orElse<OkType, ErrType>(foo)
    36Ôćĺ  ```
    37Ôćĺ
    38Ôćĺ  This only applies if type arguments were
    39Ôćĺ  explicitly provided at an orElse callsite.
    40Ôćĺ  If the type arguments were inferred,
    41Ôćĺ  no updates are needed during the upgrade.
    42Ôćĺ
